{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "join_disaggregation_m2m",
    "description": "M2 cross-binding conformance fixture (RFC semiring-faq-unified-ir §5.3; bead ess-my4.2.5). A TRUE value-equality (data-derived) join exercising the DEFINED many-to-many cardinality: a key occurring m times on the left and n times on the right contributes all m*n product terms (categorical disaggregation, ESI). Two categorical key sets share the member value \"coal\" with multiplicity 2 on each side: `sources` = [coal, coal, oil], `factors` = [coal, coal, gas]. The join on [[i,j]] (i from sources, j from factors) admits a term iff member(sources[i]) == member(factors[j]) by Unicode code point. matched = (coal i's {1,2}) x (coal j's {1,2}) = 2*2 = 4; oil and gas are unmatched (contribute the additive identity 0-bar). With the constant body 1 under sum_product the scalar reduction COUNTS the admitted combinations: count(1) = 4 from a zero IC (vs 3*3 = 9 for the join-free full product), pinning the m*n cardinality. EVALUATED BY JULIA AND PYTHON: this non-positional value-equality join is the data-derived engine the dense Rust evaluator does not yet drive (M3 — Rust treats a loop-index key column as the degenerate positional no-op and would compute the full 9, so it is name-gated out of the Rust conformance suite; the inline expected=4 is a tripwire if it is ever wired in before M3). Go/TS validate the additive join schema. See join_disaggregation_m2m_permuted.esm for the determinism (order-independence) twin.",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.nux"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "aggregate",
      "join",
      "semiring",
      "sum_product",
      "many-to-many",
      "cardinality",
      "disaggregation",
      "esi",
      "conformance",
      "ess-my4.2.5"
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "Disaggregation": {
      "tolerance": {
        "rel": 1e-6,
        "abs": 1e-9
      },
      "index_sets": {
        "sources": {
          "kind": "categorical",
          "members": ["coal", "coal", "oil"]
        },
        "factors": {
          "kind": "categorical",
          "members": ["coal", "coal", "gas"]
        }
      },
      "variables": {
        "count": { "type": "state", "default": 0.0 }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "D(count)/dt = sum_{i in sources, j in factors : member(i)==member(j)} 1. coal matches 2x2=4; oil/gas unmatched. count(1)=4 (full product without join = 9).",
          "lhs": { "op": "D", "args": ["count"], "wrt": "t" },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": [],
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "reduce": "+",
            "ranges": {
              "i": { "from": "sources" },
              "j": { "from": "factors" }
            },
            "join": [
              { "on": [["i", "j"]] }
            ],
            "expr": 1.0
          }
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        {
          "id": "disaggregation_m2m_t1",
          "description": "Many-to-many value-equality join: the shared key \"coal\" (multiplicity 2 left, 2 right) yields 2*2=4 admitted product terms; oil and gas are unmatched. count(1)=4.",
          "initial_conditions": { "count": 0.0 },
          "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
          "assertions": [
            { "variable": "count", "time": 1.0, "expected": 4.0 }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
